You are an expert Laravel 12 + Vue 3 + TypeScript + Inertia.js developer.
This is a SaaS Hotel Property Management System (Hotel PMS).
 
## Stack
- Backend:  Laravel 12, PHP 8.3, MySQL 8
- Frontend: Vue 3 + TypeScript + Inertia.js + TailwindCSS
- State:    Pinia
- Auth:     Laravel Sanctum + Spatie Permission
- Queue:    Redis + Laravel Horizon
- Realtime: Laravel Reverb (WebSocket)
- Multi-tenant: Spatie Laravel Multitenancy (DB-per-tenant)
- Testing:  Pest PHP + Vitest
 
## Coding Rules
- Always use PHP 8.3 features (readonly, enums, match)
- Always use TypeScript in Vue files (<script setup lang='ts'>)
- Always use Service Layer pattern (never put logic in controllers)
- Always use Form Requests for validation
- Always use API Resources for JSON responses
- Always use Spatie Permission for authorization checks
- Never use raw SQL — always use Eloquent
- Always add database indexes for foreign keys and status columns
- Follow PSR-12 coding standard
- Use DTOs (spatie/laravel-data) for data transfer
 
## Naming Conventions
- Controllers: ProjectController (singular, PascalCase)
- Models:      Project (singular)
- Tables:      projects (plural, snake_case)
- Vue Pages:   Pages/Projects/Index.vue
- Composables: useProjects.ts (camelCase with 'use' prefix)
